title: Grateful Dead Live at Hollywood Palladium on 1972-09-10
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, Mississippi Half Step, Black Throated Wind, Bird Song, Promised Land, Deal, El Paso, Sugaree, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones

Set 2

He's Gone-> Truckin', Ramble On Rose, Beat It On Down The Line, Black Peter, Dark Star*-> Drums-> Jack Straw*-> Sing Me Back Home*, Sugar Magnolia*, E: One More Saturday Night

*w/ David Crosby

reviews.review_text: Hollywood this is a welcome change as far as enhanced shows go, too many people try to over-enhance things sometimes, curating the most original recording and sharing it is awesome (anyone can fool with the EQ while they're listening to it on their own but please leave mine alone with your boost or whatever you're talking about).  This recording is alive, every time I stream it it seems like the player responds to the sounds the band is making in a different way over and over again until it gets one complete stream where it shows how right on the band was, Jerry's lyrics are perfect...for example.
